SENATE CHAMBER
STATE OF OKLAHOMA DISPOSITION
FLOOR AMENDMENT No. ________
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
(Date)
I move to amend House Bill No. 3015 on Page 7, Line 18 1/2, by inserting a new Section 12 to read
as follows, by amending the title to conform, and renumbering subsequent section:
“SECTION 12. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified in the Oklahoma Statutes
as Section 110 of Title 75A, unless there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
A. As used in this section, “electronic credential” shall have the same meaning as that
provided for in Section 3 of this act.
B. No person shall be denied access to the services of any agency, department, or political
subdivision of this state, or any building operated by such, on the basis of not possessing or utilizing
an electronic credential.
C. No person shall be denied service by a business or private entity in this state on the basis of
not possessing or utilizing an electronic credential.”
